in Tokyo.\", \"from\": 3254, \"to\": 3335, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3254, \"end\": 3267, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Molly_Caudery\", \"score\": 0.999995872758395, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Molly Caudery\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Molly_Caudery\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Molly_Caudery\"}, {\"begin\": 3329, \"end\": 3334, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.8975011877285911, \"rank\": 0.11420465361521244, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's not the Olympics without some velodrome shenanigans and the keirin is the best of that.\", \"from\": 3337, \"to\": 3429, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Sat behind the little man on a bike for a number of laps, this discipline is all about tactics.\", \"from\": 3430, \"to\": 3525, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"World and European champion Emma Finucane will go for Team GB.\", \"from\": 3527, \"to\": 3589, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3537, \"end\": 3554, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/European_Athletics_Championships\", \"score\": 0.9752491082045278, \"rank\": 0.0253790458122607, \"text\": \"European champion\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/European_Athletics_Championships\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/European_Athletics_Championships\"}, {\"begin\": 3555, \"end\": 3559, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tenille_Dashwood\", \"score\": 0.9997562853860016, \"rank\": 0.00024374923893406977, \"text\": \"Emma\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13474373\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tenille_Dashwood\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tenille_Dashwood\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She said: \\\"Since coming into sprinting in the last two or three years, I have massively looked up to Vicky and Becky, who is Welsh too, which is really special.\", \"from\": 3591, \"to\": 3751, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3716, \"end\": 3721, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wales_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.9969856216319829, \"rank\": 0.0024809418158845634, \"text\": \"Welsh\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wales_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wales_national_rugby_union_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I have got a really long way to go to be anywhere close to them because they are huge and they have done so much for the women's programme.\", \"from\": 3753, \"to\": 3893, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's exciting that it's come back around now.\", \"from\": 3895, \"to\": 3941, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We are no longer the weakest link in British cycling, we are producing medals and great times and we are up there.\", \"from\": 3942, \"to\": 4056, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3979, \"end\": 3994, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Cycling\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"British cycling\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Cycling\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Cycling\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am really excited to see what happens in Paris, and there is still a lot of work to do.\\\"\", \"from\": 4058, \"to\": 4149, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4102, \"end\": 4107, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.584792822080896e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'The fastest women in the world' \\u26a1\\ufe0fGB's Emma Finucane claimed her first major title as she took gold in the women's sprint at the Cycling World Championships \\ud83d\\udd25She's only 20 \\ud83e\\udd2f#GlasgowScotland2023pic.twitter.com/iXVTkZEfHU  This is female sprinting's best shot at a gold medal.\", \"from\": 4151, \"to\": 4426, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4191, \"end\": 4195, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tenille_Dashwood\", \"score\": 0.9997562853860016, \"rank\": 0.00024374923893406977, \"text\": \"Emma\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13474373\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tenille_Dashwood\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tenille_Dashwood\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"If the athletes have not been successful in the 100m, 200m or 400m then this event could be the one for the Brits.\", \"from\": 4427, \"to\": 4541, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They are stacked with depth and, should some of the competitors be slightly off it, could pounce on a medal.\", \"from\": 4543, \"to\": 4651, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They set themselves up well with a meeting record at the London Diamond League in July.\", \"from\": 4653, \"to\": 4740, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4712, \"end\": 4718, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.9993827833774869, \"rank\": 0.000617594636552218, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}, {\"begin\": 4719, \"end\": 4733, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Diamond_League\", \"score\": 0.999961331859622, \"rank\": 3.8669635509443706e-05, \"text\": \"Diamond League\", \"types\": [\"Q623109\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Diamond_League\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Diamond_League\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Britain have a superb history in boxing at the Olympics with the likes of Anthony Joshua continuing to make headlines after his medal at London 2012.\", \"from\": 4742, \"to\": 4891, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4744, \"end\": 4751, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.99999